# SKILL: Registry Crawling Pipeline
*Portable skill for crawling carbon registries (Verra VCS, Puro.earth, Isometric).*
*Tested on: clearsky-api Worker, 4,903 Verra projects, 2,116 with VCU data*

## Verra VCS OData API
```
POST https://registry.verra.org/uiapi/resource/resource/search?$count=true&$skip=N&$top=N&$filter=...
Body: {"program":"VCS"}
Response: { totalCount, value: [{ resourceIdentifier, resourceName, resourceStatusId, country, region, ... }] }
```

### OData Filter Construction
```javascript
function buildVerraFilter(params) {
  // Verra OData: NO toLower() support. Use eq for exact, contains() for partial.
  const clauses = [];

  // Status — normalize to exact Verra Title Case strings
  const STATUS_MAP = {
    'registered': 'Registered',
    'under_validation': 'Under validation',
    'under_development': 'Under development',
    'registration_requested': 'Registration and verification approval requested'
  };
  if (params.status) clauses.push(`resourceStatus eq '${STATUS_MAP[params.status.toLowerCase()] || params.status}'`);

  // Country — exact match, Title Case
  if (params.country) clauses.push(`country eq '${titleCase(params.country)}'`);

  // Project type — contains match on methodology subcategories
  if (params.projectType) clauses.push(`contains(protocolSubCategories, '${params.projectType}')`);

  // Name search — contains match
  if (params.query) clauses.push(`contains(resourceName, '${params.query}')`);

  // Project ID — exact match on resourceIdentifier
  if (params.project_id) clauses.push(`resourceIdentifier eq ${params.project_id}`);

  return clauses.join(' and ') || null;
}
```

**OData Gotchas:**
- `toLower()` is NOT supported — always use Title Case for country/status
- `contains()` works for partial string matching
- `eq` works for exact match (no quotes for numbers)
- Status values: "Under development", "Under validation", "Registration and verification approval requested", "Registered"

### Pagination
```javascript
async function crawlVerra(runId, config, env) {
  const pageSize = Math.min(config.page_size || 50, 250);
  let skip = 0, projectsFound = 0;
  while (projectsFound < maxProjects) {
    const url = `https://registry.verra.org/uiapi/resource/resource/search?$count=true&$skip=${skip}&$top=${pageSize}&$filter=${filter}`;
    const resp = await fetch(url, { method: 'POST', headers: { 'Content-Type': 'application/json' }, body: '{"program":"VCS"}' });
    const data = await resp.json();
    // Process data.value array → INSERT into crawl_projects
    skip += pageSize;
    if (data.value.length < pageSize) break;
  }
}
```

## Document Classification — 25 patterns
```javascript
function classifyVerraDoc(fileName) {
  const fl = (fileName || '').toLowerCase();
  // Registry-level documents (15 types)
  if (/methodology|^vm\d|^ams-|^acm\d/i.test(fl)) return 'core_methodology';
  if (/validation.*report|vali.*rep/i.test(fl)) return 'validation_report';
  if (/verification.*report|veri.*rep/i.test(fl)) return 'verification_report';
  if (/monitoring.*report|monitor.*rep/i.test(fl)) return 'monitoring_report';
  if (/registration.*request|reg.*req/i.test(fl)) return 'registration_request';
  if (/issuance.*request|iss.*req/i.test(fl)) return 'issuance_request';
  if (/issuance.*rep/i.test(fl)) return 'issuance_representation';
  if (/listing.*rep/i.test(fl)) return 'listing_representation';
  if (/completion/i.test(fl)) return 'completion_representation';
  if (/afolu.*pool/i.test(fl)) return 'afolu_pool_description';
  if (/buffer.*determination/i.test(fl)) return 'buffer_determination';
  if (/ccb|ccba|sd.*vista/i.test(fl)) return 'ccb_document';
  if (/stakeholder|consultation/i.test(fl)) return 'stakeholder_consultation';
  if (/prior.*consideration/i.test(fl)) return 'prior_consideration';
  if (/withdrawal/i.test(fl)) return 'withdrawal_request';

  // Project-level documents (10 types)
  if (/proj(ect)?[\s_.-]*desc|^pdd\b|^pd\b.*\d{4}|project.*design/i.test(fl)) return 'project_description';
  if (/draft.?pdd/i.test(fl)) return 'project_description';
  // ... etc.

  return 'other_document';
}
```

## PD-Only Filter (Project Description documents)
```javascript
const PD_PATTERNS = [
  /proj(ect)?[\s_.-]*desc/i,
  /\bpdd\b/i,
  /\bpd\b.*\d{4}/i,
  /project.*design/i,
  /design.*document/i,
  /draft.?pdd/i,
];

function isPdDocument(fileName) {
  return PD_PATTERNS.some(p => p.test(fileName || ''));
}
```

## D1 Schema
```sql
-- crawl_runs: id, registry, status, config(JSON), projects_found, docs_found, created_at, completed_at
-- crawl_projects: id, crawl_run_id(!), registry, registry_project_id(!), project_name, project_status, country, methodology, created_at
-- crawl_documents: id, crawl_project_id, crawl_run_id, registry, registry_project_id, filename, file_url, file_size, content_type, r2_key, extracted_markdown, word_count, registry_doc_type, version, document_role, knowledge_doc_id, created_at
```

**D1 Gotchas:**
- crawl_projects uses `crawl_run_id` (NOT `run_id`)
- crawl_projects uses `registry_project_id` (NOT `project_id`)
- Always deduplicate by registry_id + filename before inserting crawl_documents

## Quality Badges
```javascript
function assignQuality(doc) {
  if (!doc.word_count) return 'pending';  // not yet extracted
  if (doc.word_count < 50) return 'red';  // likely failed extraction
  if (doc.word_count < 500) return 'amber'; // may be partial
  if (hasBinaryGarbage(doc.extracted_markdown)) return 'red';
  return 'green';  // good extraction
}
// 6 states: pending, green, amber, red, error, skip, boundary
```

## Geographic File Handling
```javascript
const BOUNDARY_EXTS = ['kml', 'kmz', 'shp', 'dbf', 'prj', 'shx', 'geojson', 'gpx'];
const SKIP_EXTS = ['zip', 'gdb', 'dwg', 'dxf'];

// Geographic files → project_boundaries table (not extraction candidates)
// Binary files → skip entirely
```

## Extraction Pipeline (crawler docs)
```
POST /api/primitives/crawler/extract
  → reads r2_key from crawl_documents
  → runs extractDocument() (native → Mistral OCR → Claude fallback)
  → writes extracted_markdown + word_count to crawl_documents
  → inserts into knowledge_docs with source_type='crawler'
  → links knowledge_doc_id
  → fire-and-forget enrichKnowledgeDocAI for tags/doc_class
  → dedup: returns already_synced if knowledge_doc_id exists
```

