## Key Endpoints
```
POST /api/primitives/crawler/run         — start crawl (registry, project_id, max_projects, download_documents, pd_only)
GET  /api/primitives/crawler/status      — list past runs
GET  /api/primitives/crawler/status/:id  — run detail + projects + documents
POST /api/primitives/crawler/extract     — extract single crawl document
GET  /api/primitives/crawler/download/:crawl_doc_id — serve PDF from R2
```

## crawler/run Correct Field Names
```json
{
  "project_id": 1234,          // NOT "query"
  "max_projects": 50,          // NOT "max"
  "download_documents": true,  // NOT "downloadFiles"
  "pd_only": true              // NOT "pdOnly"
}
```

## Category Derivation (for registry browser)
```javascript
function deriveCat(row) {
  // project_category column is ALWAYS 'ALL' (import batch label) — NEVER use
  if (row.afolu && row.afolu.trim()) return 'AFOLU';  // Nature-based
  if (/waste|landfill|methane.*avoid/i.test(row.methodology)) return 'Waste';
  if (/transport/i.test(row.methodology)) return 'Transport';
  if (/carbon.*capture|ccs|ccus|direct.*air/i.test(row.methodology)) return 'CCS';
  return 'Energy';  // Default
}
// Distribution: AFOLU 1752 / Energy 2682 / Waste 368 / Transport 100 / CCS 1
```

## Buyer Normalization
```javascript
const BUYER_NORM = {
  'Eni Upstream': 'Eni SpA',
  'Marke VW Pkw': 'Volkswagen AG',
  'CHEVRON PETROLEUM COMPANY': 'Chevron Corporation',
  'Netflix': 'Netflix Inc.',
  // ... 26 entries total
};
function normalizeBuyer(name) { return BUYER_NORM[name] || name; }
```

## Gotchas
- Verra API rejects toLower() in OData filters — always use Title Case
- ZIP files must be preserved as ArrayBuffer — do not stringify
- KML and GeoJSON → boundary file, not extraction candidate
- Always deduplicate by registry_id + filename before inserting crawl_documents
- Puro.earth and Isometric: API credentials required, stub endpoints in place
- PDF async threshold: 1MB+ → queue extraction
- Verra details API: /resource/resource/details returns 404 — use search POST with filter instead
